title: Melbourne Cup 2025: Half Yours wins as Jamie Melham follows in Michelle Payne’s footsteps
summary: Jockey Jamie Melham made history by becoming the second woman to win the Melbourne Cup, guiding Half Yours to victory. The race took place on a wet track at Flemington amidst cloudy conditions. This milestone adds to the growing recognition of female jockeys in horse racing.

title: RBA holds official interest rate at 3.6% while warning of rising house prices and rents
summary: The Reserve Bank has maintained the cash rate at 3.6%, a move that was anticipated by analysts. Major banks forecast that there will be no interest rate cuts until at least 2026. This decision reflects ongoing economic conditions and inflation concerns.

title: Almost 120 flying foxes hospitalised after giant hail smashes Queensland colony
summary: A group of injured bats has been rescued and taken to the RSPCA wildlife hospital in Brisbane's southwest. The bats have sustained serious injuries, including smashed faces and broken wings. The hospital is providing care for their rehabilitation.
